Check this once more.

533
00:48:14,766 --> 00:48:17,853
It can be dangerous to drive
after the procedure,

534
00:48:18,103 --> 00:48:19,938
so get someone to drive you.

535
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:21,148
The atmosphere's heavy.

536
00:48:22,316 --> 00:48:23,358
It's heavy.

537
00:48:24,401 --> 00:48:26,528
Like right before a storm.

538
00:48:27,779 --> 00:48:29,031
No!

539
00:48:32,826 --> 00:48:34,328
Hello, Pain Management Center.

540
00:48:36,121 --> 00:48:37,205
What?

541
00:48:39,666 --> 00:48:41,084
What's the matter?

542
00:48:42,336 --> 00:48:44,755
-What should we do?
-About what?

543
00:48:46,298 --> 00:48:47,341
It's Ms. Yoo Ri-hye.

544
00:48:48,008 --> 00:48:49,217
What about her?

545
00:48:55,432 --> 00:48:57,559
You asked how much longer...

546
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:00,520
you can be a doctor for.

547
00:49:03,899 --> 00:49:04,983
You don't have...

548
00:49:06,401 --> 00:49:07,611
much time left.

549
00:49:29,341 --> 00:49:31,385
CRIMINAL DEPARTMENT 3 PROSECUTOR

550
00:49:34,137 --> 00:49:37,140
CHAE EUN-JEONG

551
00:49:41,269 --> 00:49:42,312
Hello?

552
00:49:44,272 --> 00:49:47,025
Prosecutor Son. My hunch was right.

553
00:49:47,109 --> 00:49:50,237
I had a bad feeling,
so I came to Hanse Medical Center.

554
00:49:51,697 --> 00:49:52,572
What's she doing?

555
00:49:52,656 --> 00:49:54,032
Don't get closer.

556
00:50:09,131 --> 00:50:10,507
Today's the day.

557
00:50:11,466 --> 00:50:14,136
The day you talked about.

558
00:50:20,058 --> 00:50:21,810
Viral labyrinthitis?

559
00:50:21,893 --> 00:50:24,479
30-30-30.

560
00:50:25,939 --> 00:50:28,400
The 30-percent likelihood
that your hearing will never return.

561
00:50:28,775 --> 00:50:31,653
The 30-percent likelihood that
we'll never know if it will.

562
00:50:31,737 --> 00:50:33,947
The 30-percent likelihood
that I'll make a full recovery.

563
00:50:34,448 --> 00:50:35,449
My option is...

564
00:50:36,533 --> 00:50:38,160
a heavy dose of steroids.

565
00:50:38,493 --> 00:50:40,787
You can never take steroids.

566
00:50:43,290 --> 00:50:46,626
It'll weaken your immune system
and you'll be prone to infections.

567
00:50:47,002 --> 00:50:49,087
Don't you know how lethal
that can be to you?

568
00:50:49,838 --> 00:50:51,715
The ticking bomb could go off...

569
00:50:52,424 --> 00:50:53,842
at any time.

570
00:50:55,761 --> 00:50:58,680
I'm saying your life could be in danger.

571
00:50:58,764 --> 00:51:00,766
I won't get better if I don't get treated.

572
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:03,435
And I can no longer be a doctor.

573
00:51:03,977 --> 00:51:04,978
So what?

574
00:51:05,812 --> 00:51:07,397
Will you put your life on the line?

575
00:51:10,192 --> 00:51:11,276
Ms. Yoo.

576
00:51:12,903 --> 00:51:15,864
Our whole team is right by your side.

577
00:51:27,626 --> 00:51:28,668
You said...

578
00:51:29,628 --> 00:51:32,214
you'd help me with anything.

579
00:51:33,006 --> 00:51:36,218
Yes. We'll help with anything.
Just tell us what you want.

580
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:50,232
You can choose
how much time you have left.

581
00:51:56,363 --> 00:51:59,366
Give up on being a doctor
and you'll live longer.

582
00:52:00,992 --> 00:52:02,577
Choose to be a doctor...

583
00:52:03,328 --> 00:52:05,664
and you must risk
all the time you have left.

584
00:52:06,832 --> 00:52:10,168
Is your career as a doctor
your whole life?

585
00:52:14,131 --> 00:52:15,215
Coming through.

586
00:52:15,549 --> 00:52:17,050
Let us through.

587
00:52:17,592 --> 00:52:19,261
You don't feel pain.

588
00:52:19,553 --> 00:52:22,973
How do you feel about patients who do?

589
00:52:24,099 --> 00:52:25,016
Do you feel pity?

590
00:52:26,017 --> 00:52:27,185
Or is it curiosity?

591
00:52:37,571 --> 00:52:38,780
How can we help you?

592
00:52:39,406 --> 00:52:42,242
We can give you more medicine
to reduce the pain.

593
00:52:43,285 --> 00:52:45,412
We can operate on you a few more times.

594
00:52:45,912 --> 00:52:49,958
None of that will cure me.

595
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:53,128
My face...

596
00:52:54,254 --> 00:52:57,382
won't come back to normal.

597
00:52:59,426 --> 00:53:00,468
Doctor.

598
00:53:02,387 --> 00:53:03,555
I didn't want to...

599
00:53:05,473 --> 00:53:07,017
have this illness.

600
00:53:08,226 --> 00:53:10,687
Yes. I know that.

601
00:53:12,147 --> 00:53:13,064
Then at least...

602
00:53:14,357 --> 00:53:16,151
can't you let me...

603
00:53:17,235 --> 00:53:18,653
choose to...

604
00:53:21,323 --> 00:53:22,616
free myself from it?

605
00:53:24,492 --> 00:53:25,619
My son...

606
00:53:27,078 --> 00:53:28,580
told me...

607
00:53:32,292 --> 00:53:34,127
that I was the prettiest in the world.

608
00:53:36,129 --> 00:53:37,380
I want him...

609
00:53:39,549 --> 00:53:41,468
to remember me that way.

610
00:53:45,138 --> 00:53:46,473
So, doctor...

611
00:53:48,016 --> 00:53:49,226
Help me.

612
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:51,770
Help me...

613
00:53:53,438 --> 00:53:55,398
end this pain...

614
00:53:57,067 --> 00:53:58,944
without having to jump.

615
00:54:07,118 --> 00:54:10,372
PROSECUTOR SON SEOK-KI

616
00:54:30,433 --> 00:54:32,185
I guess you can't.

617
00:54:39,484 --> 00:54:40,610
Don't die.

618
00:54:43,363 --> 00:54:44,698
Not this kind of wish.

619
00:54:46,157 --> 00:54:48,410
How can we grant something like that?

620
00:54:49,911 --> 00:54:51,037
How?

621
00:54:53,373 --> 00:54:54,833
Please don't do this.

622
00:55:08,013 --> 00:55:09,222
Doctors.

623
00:55:10,807 --> 00:55:11,891
Sometimes,

624
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:14,311
telling one not to die...

625
00:55:18,148 --> 00:55:19,399
is even worse...

626
00:55:22,527 --> 00:55:24,070
than telling them to die.

627
00:55:59,356 --> 00:56:00,774
We have to pull ourselves together.

628
00:56:17,332 --> 00:56:18,166
Move!

629
00:56:19,084 --> 00:56:20,168
Coming through!

630
00:56:21,336 --> 00:56:23,588
This way. How is she?

631
00:56:23,671 --> 00:56:24,672
There's no breathing.

632
00:56:30,345 --> 00:56:31,679
The oxygen saturation level is 78.

633
00:56:31,763 --> 00:56:33,890
Because of nasal bleeding,
intubation will be difficult.

634
00:56:34,682 --> 00:56:35,892
Laryngeal mask.

635
00:56:44,359 --> 00:56:45,235
Ambu bag.

636
00:56:53,034 --> 00:56:55,161
Hold on. How is she?

637
00:56:55,245 --> 00:56:57,247
Bleeding from nasal tumor
caused respiratory failure.

638
00:57:04,963 --> 00:57:06,172
Move her to the emergency room.

639
00:57:07,882 --> 00:57:09,092
Coming through.

640
00:57:21,646 --> 00:57:23,022
That way.

641
00:57:30,864 --> 00:57:32,449
Ri-hye. Ri-hye.

642
00:57:32,824 --> 00:57:35,201
It's your sister, Ri-hye.

643
00:57:37,162 --> 00:57:38,288
Ri-hye.

644
00:57:41,875 --> 00:57:43,710
I'm sorry, but you can't enter.

645
00:58:38,264 --> 00:58:39,516
We have a problem.

646
00:58:39,933 --> 00:58:42,519
-Yoo Ri-hye.
-What is it now?

647
00:58:43,811 --> 00:58:46,648
Someone turned off her ventilator.

648
00:58:48,691 --> 00:58:49,692
What?

649
00:58:52,195 --> 00:58:53,321
Who?

650
00:58:56,824 --> 00:58:58,034
Who are you?

651
00:59:32,026 --> 00:59:33,528
-Dr. Cha?
-Dr. Cha?

652
00:59:37,574 --> 00:59:40,076
Find the culprit through
an investigation, not guesses.

653
00:59:40,159 --> 00:59:42,287
The police are on their way here.
The police!

654
00:59:42,370 --> 00:59:44,289
This is clearly attempted murder.

655
00:59:44,372 --> 00:59:46,374
Lieutenant Kim Jung-rok
from Gangnam Police Station.

656
00:59:46,457 --> 00:59:48,251
Don't say anything
until the truth is revealed.

657
00:59:48,334 --> 00:59:50,545
No. I will cooperate
with the investigation

658
00:59:50,628 --> 00:59:51,838
like I did three years ago.

659
00:59:51,921 --> 00:59:53,715
The investigation will be conducted
by who?

660
00:59:53,798 --> 00:59:55,675
All interrogations and interviews
will be done...

661
00:59:55,883 --> 00:59:57,677
by Prosecutor Son Seok-ki.

